{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0ad3a417-5794-4a84-8abe-54d0b817dbfd","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. Could you provide the path to your dump file?\n\nIn the meantime, here's a quick overview of tools you can use to analyze a .NET crash dump:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — Interactive CLI tool for managed .NET dumps. Key commands:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stacks\n   - `pe` (PrintException) — show exception details\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **`lldb` + SOS plugin** — For mixed native/managed analysis on Linux.\n\n3. **Visual Studio** — Open the `.dmp` directly on Windows for a rich UI experience.\n\n4. **WinDbg + SOS/SOSEX** — Classic Windows debugger with `!analyze -v`, `!clrstack`, `!pe`.\n\n**To proceed**, either:\n- Drop/copy the `.dmp` file into this directory, or\n- Tell me its full path\n\nand I'll walk through the analysis with `dotnet-dump`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"21147aee-7ab5-43b0-84ca-98b58520c0b3","outputTokens":262,"requestId":"A040:276D2D:927CD6:B5A525:6A01382B"},"id":"02f9bb28-dce2-4e8c-affb-377360ceb93d","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:00:19.007Z","parentId":"c8771c62-92c6-4d54-91a2-7b68d0ea2a36"}
